      • createShift

        public ResultShiftDto createShift(@NotNull
                                  @NotNull ShiftDto shiftDto)
                           throws org.springframework.security.core.userdetails.UsernameNotFoundException,
                                  ShiftIllegalArgumentException
        Creates the shift for a given user

        Does the below validations: 1. The username given in ShiftDto is an existing username 2. The shift's start time is not the same as the shift's end time 3. The shift's end time is not set before the shift's start time 4. The updated shift does not overlap with another shift of the user

        Parameters:
        shiftDto - the ShiftDto providing parameters for creating the shift
        Returns:
        the result of the shift creation
        Throws:
        org.springframework.security.core.userdetails.UsernameNotFoundException - when the specified user does not exist
        ShiftIllegalArgumentException - when the given params from the shiftDto violates rules listed in the method description

      • updateShift

        public ResultShiftDto updateShift(@NotNull
                                  @NotNull long shiftId,
                                  @NotNull
                                  @NotNull ShiftDto shiftDto)
                           throws ShiftNotFoundException,
                                  ShiftIllegalArgumentException,
                                  org.springframework.security.core.userdetails.UsernameNotFoundException
        Updates the shift for the given user

        Does the below validations: 1. The username given in ShiftDto is an existing username 2. The shift's start time is not the same as the shift's end time 3. The shift's end time is not set before the shift's start time 4. The updated shift does not overlap with another shift of the user

        Parameters:
        shiftId - the shift to be updated
        shiftDto - the updated parameters ShiftDto. A username must be specified here (or it will default to the currently logged in user) in order to do rule validations
        Returns:
        the result of the shift update
        Throws:
        ShiftNotFoundException - when there is no shift existing for the given username with the given id
        ShiftIllegalArgumentException - when the given params from the shiftDto violates rules listed in the method description
        org.springframework.security.core.userdetails.UsernameNotFoundException - when the specified user does not exist
